  "prompt": "What are the things you can do on your 23rd Birthday?",
  "response": "Your 23rd birthday is a great milestone! Here's a breakdown of things you can do, categorized by interests and budget:\n\n**General Celebration Ideas (Regardless of Interests):**\n\n*   **Dinner & Drinks:**\n    *   **Restaurant:** Go to your favorite restaurant or try a new one.\n    *   **Home Cooked Meal:** Cook a special meal with friends or family.\n    *   **Bar/Club:** Hit up your favorite bar or club for a night of dancing and drinks.\n    *   **Brewery/Winery Tour:** Sample local brews or wines with a group.\n*   **Party:**\n    *   **Themed Party:** Choose a fun theme (e.g., decades, Hollywood, costume) and have guests dress up.\n    *   **Casual Gathering:** Host a casual party at your place with games, music, and food.\n    *   **Outdoor Party:** If the weather's nice, have a barbecue or picnic in a park.\n*   **Adventure/Activity:**\n    *   **Escape Room:** Test your problem-solving skills with friends.\n    *   **Go-Karting/Bowling/Arcade:** Classic fun activities.\n    *   **Hiking/Outdoor Adventure:** Explore a local trail or park.\n    *   **Concert/Show:** See your favorite band or a play.\n    *   **Sporting Event:** Catch a game with friends.\n*   **Relaxation/Self-Care:**\n    *   **Spa Day:** Pamper yourself with a massage, facial, or manicure/pedicure.\n    *   **Staycation:** Book a night at a local hotel and relax.\n    *   **Movie Marathon:** Watch your favorite movies at home.\n\n**Ideas Based on Interests:**\n\n*   **For the Foodie:**\n    *   **Cooking Class:** Learn to make a new dish.\n    *   **Food Tour:** Explore different restaurants and cuisines in your city.\n    *   **Wine/Beer Tasting:** Visit a local winery or brewery.\n    *   **Fancy Dinner:** Treat yourself to a high-end dining experience.\n*   **For the Adventurer:**\n    *   **Road Trip:** Explore a new place.\n    *   **Camping/Hiking:** Spend time in nature.\n    *   **Rock Climbing/Ziplining:** Get your adrenaline pumping.\n    *   **Water Sports:** Go kayaking, paddleboarding, or surfing.\n*   **For the Creative:**\n    *   **Art Class:** Take a painting, pottery, or photography class.\n    *   **Visit a Museum/Art Gallery:** Get inspired by art and culture.\n    *   **Write/Compose Music:** Dedicate some time to your creative pursuits.\n    *   **Attend an Open Mic Night:** Share your talents.\n*   **For the Homebody:**\n    *   **Game Night:** Play board games or video games with friends.\n    *   **Movie Marathon:** Watch your favorite films.\n    *   **Read a New Book:** Curl up with a good book.\n    *   **Bake a Cake:** Create a delicious treat.\n*   **For the Social Butterfly:**\n    *   **Large Party:** Invite all your friends and family.\n    *   **Bar Crawl:** Explore different bars in your city.\n    *   **Karaoke Night:** Sing your heart out.\n\n**Ideas Based on Budget:**\n\n*   **Budget-Friendly:**\n    *   **Potluck:** Have friends bring dishes to share.\n    *   **Picnic:** Pack a lunch and head to a park.\n    *   **Game Night:** Play board games or video games at home.\n    *   **DIY Spa Day:** Give each other manicures, face masks, etc.\n    *   **Free Events:** Look for free concerts, festivals, or museum days in your area.\n*   **Mid-Range:**\n    *   **Restaurant Dinner:** Go to a nice but not super expensive restaurant.\n    *   **Concert/Show:** See a local band or a less expensive show.\n    *   **Day Trip:** Explore a nearby town or attraction.\n    *   **Escape Room/Go-Karting:** Have some fun with friends.\n*   **Splurge:**\n    *   **Luxury Hotel Stay:** Pamper yourself with a night at a fancy hotel.\n    *   **Fine Dining Experience:** Go to a top-rated restaurant.\n    *   **Weekend Getaway:** Travel to a new city or country.\n    *   **High-End Concert/Show:** See your favorite artist in style.\n\n**Remember to Consider:**\n\n*   **Your personality:** Choose something that you'll genuinely enjoy.\n*   **Your budget:** Set a budget beforehand and stick to it.\n*   **Your friends and family:** Include them in your celebration if you want.\n*   **The time of year:** Plan accordingly for the weather.\n*   **Your health and safety:** Drink responsibly, wear a mask if needed, and be aware of your surroundings.\n\nNo matter what you choose to do, the most important thing is to celebrate your 23rd birthday in a way that makes you happy!\n",
